- Roots need oxygen, need to live in aerobic environment
- Deciduous plants make good roots
	- But are unappealing to sell cause they die in fall
- Roots can only grow where there is water and oxygen
	- Typically the first foot or so of the soil
- Roots *cannot* grow in cold soil
	- Early planting isnt viable unless soil has significant sand content
		- Plants planted later at appropriate times tend to fruit better/earlier
-  


## Types of Roots
-  ![Monocot-and-Dicot-Roots.jpeg|200](data:image/png;base64,)

- Taproots (Dicots)

- Roots of woody plants
	- Are 3-4x the width of the canopy
		- Stretch ~1 extra canopy width away
	- ![final-tree-for-soil-water.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)
	- Root hairs form a ring around the edge of this root system
	- Have a root crown
		- The wide part at the bottom that branches out to become the roots
		- If a trunk goes straight into ground without widening, it's planted too deep

- Components
	- Root cap ^root-cap
		- Secretes lubricant and acid, capable of destroying rocks
	- Stele
	- Cortex
	- Root hair
		- Where 99% of moisture uptake happens
		- Die after 1-3 days
		- Migrate down roots as they die
		- Major microbiome
			- Called the [[Unsorted/Soil microbiology\|rhizosphere]]
			- Example members
				- Bacterium that lives in rhizoosphere, produces antifungal substances to defend against pathogens
			- Roots secrete sugars
				- Microbes and fungi love this stuff
				- Fungi give the roots water and phosphorous
					- [[Unsorted/Fungi\|Fungi]]
				- Receive sugar from tree
			- Can't purchase microrrhiza, die if soil is unplanted for too long
		- ![Root-hair-cells-black-arrow-pointing-at-one-of-the-root-hair-cells-are-single-tubular.jpg|100](data:image/png;base64,)
		- There's a couple species of plants with no root hairs
